  "text": "HomeShoppingStore FrontCustomers can shop from brands like Kosas and Indie Lee online or at one of its two SoCal boutiques, which also offer facial treatments.Photo: Courtesy of Shop GoodStore Front is Fashionista's guide to the best independent and local fashion and beauty retailers — a resource for brands, job seekers, B2B companies and consumers alike. If you'd like your store to be featured, fill out this form.Shop GoodBrick \u0026 mortar: North Park (3027 University Ave) and Del Mar (3665 Paseo Place, Suite 960) in San Diego, CAE-commerce: shop-good.coSocial media: Instagram / TikTokWhat: An online and brick-and-mortar \"clean\"-beauty boutique with a holistic facial spa offering expert treatments.Owner: Leah KirpalaniOrigin Story: Shop Good was born from founder Leah Kirpalani's decade-long journey to heal her chronic health issues — skin, gut and hormonal — that traditional medicine alone couldn't solve. After years of piecing together her care team (from facialist to functional MD), she saw a glaring gap in the beauty space: There was no one-stop destination that merged internal wellness with external care. With a background in fashion merchandising at Gap Inc. and holistic health coaching from IIN, Leah launched Shop Good in 2017 to fill that void.What started as a single brick-and-mortar in San Diego has grown into a \"clean\" beauty and wellness destination known for expert-curated products, results-driven organic facials, and community-centered experiences. It blends a brick-and-mortar boutique with a holistic facial spa, so clients can seamlessly shop and experience expert treatments under one roof. Shop Good hand-selects brands that meet rigorous standards for efficacy, ingredient transparency and \"sustainability.\" It also champions refill programs, eco-friendly packaging and mindful sourcingScroll to ContinueRecommended ArticlesPhoto: Courtesy of Shop GoodThe customer: Wellness-Driven Beauty Enthusiast: Values \"clean,\" non-toxic formulations and seeks products that deliver real, skin-improving results.Holistic Lifestyle Adopter: Invests in both internal health (nutrition, supplements, self-care rituals) and external care (facials, body treatments).Informed \u0026 Curious: Researches ingredients, brand ethics and sustainability; appreciates educational events, one-on-one consultations and community masterclasses. Mid-20s to Mid-50s Professional: Typically urban or suburban, with disposable income to spend on premium beauty and wellness experiences.Eco- and Socially-Conscious Shopper: Prefers brands with transparent sourcing, refill programs, and environmentally responsible packaging.Community Seeker: Craves connection — whether through membership perks, pop-ups or in-store events — to feel part of a like-minded, wellness-focused group.Special Services: Masterclasses with founders; immersive weekend pop-ups; self-care rituals guided by experts; membership program offering exclusive benefits like priority booking, member-only events and curated product drops.In stock: Cosmetics, skin care, hair care, fragrance and wellness products by brands like Ilia Beauty, Kosas, Osea Malibu, Indie Lee, Marie Veronique and Therabody.How to get in touch: dreamteam@shop-good.co (jobs), hello@shop-good.co (business)Want your store featured? Hit the link below.Fashionista is the leading online destination for current and aspiring fashion and beauty industry professionals. Reach businesses, students and consumers alike with our range of digital offerings.Subscribe to Our Newsletter",
