ickEvent(this, event);\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eTikTok\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat: \u003c/strong\u003eAn online and brick-and-mortar \u0026#34;clean\u0026#34;-beauty boutique with a holistic facial spa offering expert treatments.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOwner: \u003c/strong\u003eLeah Kirpalani\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrigin Story: \u003c/strong\u003eShop Good was born from founder Leah Kirpalani\u0026#39;s decade-long journey to heal her chronic health issues — skin, gut and hormonal — that traditional medicine alone couldn\u0026#39;t solve. After years of piecing together her care team (from facialist to functional MD), she saw a glaring gap in the beauty space: There was no one-stop destination that merged internal wellness with external care. With a background in fashion merchandising at \u003ca href=\"https://fashionista.com/designers/gap\"\u003eGap\u003c/a\u003e Inc. and holistic health coaching from IIN, Leah launched Shop Good in 2017 to fill that void.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhat started as a single brick-and-mortar in San Diego has grown into a \u0026#34;clean\u0026#34; beauty and wellness destination known for expert-curated products, results-driven organic facials, and community-centered experiences. It blends a brick-and-mortar boutique with a holistic facial spa, so clients can seamlessly shop and experience expert treatments under one roof. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eShop Good hand-selects brands that meet rigorous standards for efficacy, ingredient transparency and \u0026#34;\u003ca href=\"https://fashionista.com/tag/sustainability\"\u003esustainability\u003c/a\u003e.\u0026#34; It also champions refill programs, eco-friendly packaging and mindful sourcing\u003c/p\u003e\u003csection id=\"phx-3\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eScroll to Continue\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"phx-5\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 role=\"heading\" aria-level=\"2\"\u003eRecommende